Karana</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kellory>Kellory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Sexless Drood Watchman</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/10/01 3:48:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=213.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Planes leader</span><hr size=1> For starters, I see no reason why things have to continue immediatly as they are.  There is no reason why we cant take a couple of weeks or a month to relax everyone before finding someone else.  I figure eventually someone will step up for the same reason KCoG was originally formed.  Because someday someone will get bored and step forward.  Rushing things or finding a stopgap is only going to serve as a temporary solution.  No reason why we cant wait till a permanent solution comes to us.<br>
<br>
I would point out, my last raid was only 4 days ago.  We're still at the bottom of the rotation at the KGC in any event.  And will be so for another couple of weeks.  We had a 2-3 week vacation from plane raids coming up anyway.<br>
<br>
These raids are going to continue its because someone is going to step forward and say I'll do it.  Not because someone suggests a way someone else might be able to do it.  It might be tomorrow, it might be next month, it might be next January.  But eventually someone will.  KCoG was formed not to be a parasite organization, but as a means to help small guilds team together to take on large targets without having to form an uber guild or lose players to those uber guilds.  If that premise is still sound, then someone will step forward.  If isnt, then perhaps its time to let KCoG go.<br>
<br>
Neither the planes nor the dragons are going anywhere.  I'd prefer to find a permanent solution rather than a stop gap myself.  But thats just me.  I'm still waiting for someone, anyone, to say I'll do it, lets get together and plan it out.<br>
<br>
Kellory Silverstar<br>
